msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1230
msgid ""
"Returns the identifier of the item before *item* (a previous sibling or the "
"parent of *item*), or '' if there is none. By default only visible items are "
"considered; if *hidden* is true, hidden items are included too. If *recurse* "
"is false, only siblings of *item* are considered (see :meth:`prev`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1245
msgid "Returns the number of levels between *item* and the root item."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1254
msgid "Returns ``True`` if *item* has children, ``False`` otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1263
msgid ""
"Returns ``True`` if *item* is visible, ``False`` otherwise. An item is "
"visible if it is not detached, not hidden, and all of its ancestors are open "
"and not hidden."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1274
msgid ""
"Returns the number of children of *item*. If *hidden* is true, hidden items "
"are included. If *recurse* is true, all descendants of *item* are included. "
"Use ``''`` for the root item. ``size(item, hidden=True)`` equals "
"``len(get_children(item))`` (which always includes hidden items)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1288
msgid ""
"Returns a tuple of items from *first* through *last*, inclusive. If *hidden* "
"is true, hidden items are included. If *recurse* is false, descendants and "
"ancestors are excluded."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1299
msgid ""
"Returns the identifier of the item at *index* within *item*'s list of "
"children."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1309
msgid ""
"Returns the current item id and column id as a 2-tuple, or an empty tuple if "
"there is none. The current item is the item under the mouse pointer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1320
msgid ""
"Set all of the specified items to the open state. If *recurse* is true, also "
"open all of their descendants; this requires Tk 9.1. Use ``''`` for the root "
"item. ``expand(item)`` is equivalent to ``item(item, open=True)``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1331
msgid ""
"Set all of the specified items to the closed state. If *recurse* is true, "
"also close all of their descendants; this requires Tk 9.1. Use ``''`` for "
"the root item. ``collapse(item)`` is equivalent to ``item(item, "
"open=False)``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1342
msgid ""
"Hide all of the specified items and all of their child items. If *recurse* "
"is true, also hide all of their descendants. Use ``''`` for the root item. "
"``hide(item)`` is equivalent to ``item(item, hidden=True)``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1354
msgid ""
"Unhide all of the specified items. If *recurse* is true, also unhide all of "
"their descendants. Use ``''`` for the root item. ``unhide(item)`` is "
"equivalent to ``item(item, hidden=False)``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1366
msgid ""
"Returns information about detached items (see :meth:`detach`). Without "
"arguments, returns a tuple of all detached items, but not their descendants "
"(see :meth:`detached_all`). With *item*, returns whether *item* is detached; "
"since Tk 9.1, also returns true if an ancestor of *item* is detached."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1373
msgid "Requires Tk 9.0 or newer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1380
msgid ""
"Returns a tuple of all detached items and all of their descendants (see :"
"meth:`detach`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1390
msgid ""
"Get or set the focus cell. Without *cell*, returns the focus cell as an "
"``(item, column)`` 2-tuple, or an empty tuple if there is none. With *cell*, "
"sets the focus cell; use ``''`` to clear it. A cell is specified as an "
"``(item, column)`` pair."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1403
msgid ""
"Sort the children of *parent*. By default the children are sorted by the "
"value of the first display column, as Unicode strings, in increasing order. "
"*column* selects the column to sort on. *dictionary*, *integer* and *real* "
"select the comparison type; *nocase* makes string comparison case-"
"insensitive. *command* is a function of two values returning a negative, "
"zero or positive number. *decreasing* reverses the order. *ignoreempty* "
"skips empty values (with *integer* or *real*). *recurse* also sorts all "
"descendants."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1422
msgid ""
"Search *parent*'s children for *pattern* and return the identifier of the "
"first matching item, or ``''`` if there is no match. By default *pattern* is "
"matched for exact equality against the value of each displayed column, as "
"Unicode strings, searching forwards through the direct children of *parent*. "
"*glob* or *regexp* select glob-style or regular expression matching; "
"*dictionary*, *integer* and *real* select the comparison type; *nocase* "
"makes it case-insensitive. *columns* limits the search to the given columns. "
"*start* and *stop* bound the search; *backwards* reverses its direction; "
"*wraparound* continues from the other end. *hidden* also searches hidden and "
"closed items; *recurse* searches all descendants."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1438
msgid ""
"See :meth:`search_all`, :meth:`search_cell` and :meth:`search_all_cells`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1447
msgid ""
"Like :meth:`search`, but returns a tuple of the identifiers of all matching "
"items."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1457
msgid ""
"Like :meth:`search`, but returns the first matching cell as an ``(item, "
"column)`` 2-tuple, or an empty tuple if there is no match."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1468
msgid ""
"Like :meth:`search`, but returns a tuple of all matching cells, each an "
"``(item, column)`` 2-tuple."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1479
msgid ""
"Returns a tuple of the selected cells, each an ``(item, column)`` 2-tuple. "
"The cell selection is independent from the item selection (see :meth:"
"`selection`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1491
msgid ""
"The specified cells become the new cell selection. Each cell is an ``(item, "
"column)`` pair. Call without arguments to clear the cell selection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1502
msgid "Add the specified cells to the cell selection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1511
msgid "Remove the specified cells from the cell selection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1520
msgid ""
"Set the cell selection to the rectangle of cells from *first* to *last*. "
"*first* and *last* are the opposite corner cells, each an ``(item, column)`` "
"pair, and must be in displayed columns. All other cells are unselected. If "
"*hidden* is false, hidden cells are excluded; if *recurse* is false, cells "
"in descendant items are excluded."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1534
msgid ""
"Like :meth:`cellselection_set_range`, but adds the rectangle of cells to the "
"cell selection instead of replacing it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1545
msgid ""
"Like :meth:`cellselection_set_range`, but removes the rectangle of cells "
"from the cell selection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1555
msgid ""
"Get or set the cell selection anchor. Without *cell*, returns the anchor as "
"an ``(item, column)`` 2-tuple, or an empty tuple if it is unset. With "
"*cell*, sets the anchor; use ``''`` to unset it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1567
msgid "Returns whether all of the specified cells are selected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1576
msgid "Returns whether any cell is selected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1585
msgid ""
"Add the given tag to each of the specified cells. Each cell is an ``(item, "
"column)`` pair. Cell tags are independent from item tags."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1596
msgid ""
"Remove the given tag from each of the specified cells. If no cell is "
"specified, the tag is removed from all cells."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1606
msgid ""
"Test for a cell tag, or list the cells that have it. If *cell* is specified, "
"returns whether that cell has the given tag. Otherwise returns a tuple of "
"all cells (as ``(item, column)`` 2-tuples) that have the tag."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1618
msgid "Ensure that *item* is visible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1620
msgid ""
"Sets all of *item*'s ancestors open option to ``True``, and scrolls the "
"widget if necessary so that *item* is within the visible portion of the tree."
msgstr ""

