"If \"vsapi\" is used as the value of *etype*, :meth:`element_create` will "
"create a new element in the current theme whose visual appearance is drawn "
"using the Microsoft Visual Styles API which is responsible for the themed "
"styles on Windows XP and Vista. *args* is expected to contain the Visual "
"Styles class and part as given in the Microsoft documentation followed by an "
"optional sequence of tuples of ttk states and the corresponding Visual "
"Styles API state value. *kw* may have the following options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1910
msgid ""
"Specify the element's interior padding. *padding* is a list of up to four "
"integers specifying the left, top, right and bottom padding quantities "
"respectively. If fewer than four elements are specified, bottom defaults to "
"top, right defaults to left, and top defaults to left. In other words, a "
"list of three numbers specify the left, vertical, and right padding; a list "
"of two numbers specify the horizontal and the vertical padding; a single "
"number specifies the same padding all the way around the widget. This option "
"may not be mixed with any other options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1921
msgid "margins=padding"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1922
msgid ""
"Specifies the elements exterior padding. *padding* is a list of up to four "
"integers specifying the left, top, right and bottom padding quantities "
"respectively. This option may not be mixed with any other options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1928
msgid ""
"Specifies the width for the element. If this option is set then the Visual "
"Styles API will not be queried for the recommended size or the part. If this "
"option is set then *height* should also be set. The *width* and *height* "
"options cannot be mixed with the *padding* or *margins* options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1936
msgid "Specifies the height of the element. See the comments for *width*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1954
msgid "Added support of the \"vsapi\" element factory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1959
msgid "Returns a tuple of elements defined in the current theme."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1964
msgid "Returns a tuple of *elementname*'s options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1969
msgid "Create a new theme."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1971
msgid ""
"It is an error if *themename* already exists. If *parent* is specified, the "
"new theme will inherit styles, elements and layouts from the parent theme. "
"If *settings* are present they are expected to have the same syntax used "
"for :meth:`theme_settings`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1979
msgid ""
"Temporarily sets the current theme to *themename*, apply specified "
"*settings* and then restore the previous theme."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1982
msgid ""
"Each key in *settings* is a style and each value may contain the keys "
"'configure', 'map', 'layout' and 'element create' and they are expected to "
"have the same format as specified by the methods :meth:`Style.configure`, :"
"meth:`Style.map`, :meth:`Style.layout` and :meth:`Style.element_create` "
"respectively."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:1988
msgid "As an example, let's change the Combobox for the default theme a bit::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2016
msgid "Returns a tuple of all known themes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2021
msgid ""
"If *themename* is not given, returns the theme in use.  Otherwise, sets the "
"current theme to *themename*, refreshes all widgets and emits a "
"<<ThemeChanged>> event."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2027
msgid "Layouts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2029
msgid ""
"A layout can be just ``None``, if it takes no options, or a dict of options "
"specifying how to arrange the element. The layout mechanism uses a "
"simplified version of the pack geometry manager: given an initial cavity, "
"each element is allocated a parcel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2036
msgid "*side*: whichside"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2037
msgid ""
"Specifies which side of the cavity to place the element; one of top, right, "
"bottom or left. If omitted, the element occupies the entire cavity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2041
msgid "*sticky*: nswe"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2042
msgid "Specifies where the element is placed inside its allocated parcel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2044
msgid "*unit*: 0 or 1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2045
msgid ""
"If set to 1, causes the element and all of its descendants to be treated as "
"a single element for the purposes of :meth:`Widget.identify` et al. It's "
"used for things like scrollbar thumbs with grips."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2049
msgid "*children*: [sublayout... ]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2050
msgid ""
"Specifies a list of elements to place inside the element. Each element is a "
"tuple (or other sequence type) where the first item is the layout name, and "
"the other is a `Layout`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2058
msgid "Additional widgets"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2060
msgid ""
"The following themed widgets complete the :mod:`tkinter.ttk` widget set. "
"Each is the themed counterpart of the like-named classic :mod:`tkinter` "
"widget and inherits the common methods of :class:`Widget`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2066
msgid ""
"Ttk :class:`Button` widget, displays a textual label and/or image, and "
"evaluates a command when pressed. It is the themed counterpart of :class:"
"`tkinter.Button` and inherits the common widget methods from :class:`Widget`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2073
msgid "Invoke the command associated with the button and return its result."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2078
msgid ""
"Ttk :class:`Checkbutton` widget, used to control a boolean variable that is "
"toggled on and off. It is the themed counterpart of :class:`tkinter."
"Checkbutton` and inherits the common widget methods from :class:`Widget`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2085
msgid ""
"Toggle the button between its selected and deselected states, invoke the "
"command associated with the button, and return its result."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2091
msgid ""
"Ttk :class:`Entry` widget, displays a one-line text string and allows the "
"user to edit it. It is the themed counterpart of :class:`tkinter.Entry` and "
"inherits the common widget methods from :class:`Widget` as well as the "
"editing methods from :class:`tkinter.Entry`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2099
msgid ""
"Return a tuple ``(x, y, width, height)`` giving the bounding box of the "
"character at the given *index*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2107
msgid ""
"Return the name of the element under the point given by *x* and *y*, or the "
"empty string if no element is present at that location."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2112
msgid ""
"Force validation of the entry and return ``True`` if validation succeeded, "
"and ``False`` otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2118
msgid ""
"Ttk :class:`Frame` widget, a container used to group and lay out other "
"widgets. It is the themed counterpart of :class:`tkinter.Frame` and inherits "
"the common widget methods from :class:`Widget`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2126
msgid ""
"Ttk :class:`Label` widget, displays a textual label and/or image. It is the "
"themed counterpart of :class:`tkinter.Label` and inherits the common widget "
"methods from :class:`Widget`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2133
msgid ""
"Ttk :class:`Labelframe` widget, a container that draws a border and a title "
"label around its contents. It is the themed counterpart of :class:`tkinter."
"LabelFrame` and inherits the common widget methods from :class:`Widget`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2141
msgid ""
"Ttk :class:`Menubutton` widget, displays a textual label and/or image, and "
"pops up a menu when pressed. It is the themed counterpart of :class:`tkinter."
"Menubutton` and inherits the common widget methods from :class:`Widget`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2149
msgid ""
"Ttk :class:`OptionMenu` widget, a :class:`Menubutton` that pops up a menu of "
"mutually exclusive choices. *variable* is the variable that tracks the "
"currently selected value, *default* is the value to set initially, and "
"*values* are the entries to display in the menu. A *command* keyword "
"argument may be given to specify a callable that is invoked with the "
"selected value whenever the selection changes; the *style* keyword argument "
"sets the style used by the underlying menubutton; and the *name* keyword "
"argument sets the Tk widget name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2161
msgid ""
"Replace the entries of the menu with *values*. If *default* is given, also "
"set it as the current value of the *variable*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2167
msgid "Destroy this widget and its associated menu."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2169
msgid "Added support for the *name* keyword argument."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2176
msgid ""
"Ttk :class:`Panedwindow` widget, displays a number of subwindows stacked "
"either vertically or horizontally. The user may adjust the relative sizes of "
"the subwindows by dragging the sash between panes. It is the themed "
"counterpart of :class:`tkinter.PanedWindow` and inherits the common widget "
"methods from :class:`Widget`, as well as the :meth:`!add` and :meth:`!panes` "
"methods from :class:`tkinter.PanedWindow`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2186
msgid ""
"Insert a pane containing *child* at the position *pos*. *pos* is either the "
"string ``'end'``, an integer index, or the name of a managed subwindow. If "
"*child* is already managed by the paned window, move it to the specified "
"position. Any keyword arguments set pane options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2195
msgid ""
"Remove *child*, which may be either an integer index or the name of a "
"managed subwindow, from the panes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2205
msgid ""
"Query or modify the options of the specified *pane*, where *pane* is either "
"an integer index or the name of a managed subwindow. If no arguments are "
"given, return a dictionary of the pane option values. If *option* is "
"specified, return the value of that option. Otherwise, set the options given "
"as keyword arguments to their corresponding values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2214
msgid ""
"If *newpos* is specified, set the position of sash number *index* and return "
"its new position. This may adjust the positions of adjacent sashes to ensure "
"that positions are monotonically increasing; positions are also constrained "
"to be between 0 and the total size of the widget. If *newpos* is omitted, "
"return the current position of the sash."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2224
msgid ""
"Ttk :class:`Radiobutton` widget, used as part of a group to control a single "
"shared variable by selecting one of several mutually exclusive values. It is "
"the themed counterpart of :class:`tkinter.Radiobutton` and inherits the "
"common widget methods from :class:`Widget`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2231
msgid ""
"Set the option variable to the button's value, select the button, invoke the "
"command associated with the button, and return its result."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2237
msgid ""
"Ttk :class:`Scale` widget, displays a slider that lets the user select a "
"numeric value from a range by moving the slider along a trough. It is the "
"themed counterpart of :class:`tkinter.Scale` and inherits the common widget "
"methods from :class:`Widget`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2244
msgid ""
"Modify or query the widget options, like :meth:`Widget.configure <tkinter."
"Misc.configure>`. In addition, this method clips the ``from`` and ``to`` "
"values so that the current value stays within the range defined by them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2249
msgid ""
"Now returns the configuration value, like :meth:`Widget.configure <tkinter."
"Misc.configure>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2256
msgid ""
"Return the current value of the scale. If *x* and *y* are given, return the "
"value corresponding to the pixel coordinate *x*, *y* instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2263
msgid ""
"Ttk :class:`Scrollbar` widget, controls the viewport of an associated "
"scrollable widget such as a :class:`Treeview`, :class:`Entry` or :class:"
"`tkinter.Text`. It is the themed counterpart of :class:`tkinter.Scrollbar` "
"and inherits the common widget methods from :class:`Widget`, as well as the :"
"meth:`!set` and :meth:`!get` methods from :class:`tkinter.Scrollbar`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2273
msgid ""
"Ttk :class:`Separator` widget, displays a horizontal or vertical separator "
"line. It has no direct counterpart in :mod:`tkinter` and inherits the common "
"widget methods from :class:`Widget`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2281
msgid ""
"Ttk :class:`Sizegrip` widget, displays a grip that allows the user to resize "
"the containing toplevel window by pressing and dragging the grip, typically "
"placed in the bottom-right corner. It has no direct counterpart in :mod:"
"`tkinter` and inherits the common widget methods from :class:`Widget`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2290
msgid ""
"A :class:`Frame` containing a :class:`Scale` and a :class:`Label` that shows "
"the scale's current value. *variable* is the :class:`~tkinter.IntVar` "
"tracked by the scale (one is created if it is not given), and *from_* and "
"*to* define the range of the scale."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2298
msgid ""
"Destroy this widget and remove the trace callback registered on the "
"associated variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2304
msgid ""
"Alias of :class:`Labelframe`, kept for naming compatibility with :class:"
"`tkinter.LabelFrame`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:2310
msgid ""
"Alias of :class:`Panedwindow`, kept for naming compatibility with :class:"
"`tkinter.PanedWindow`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.ttk.rst:9
msgid "ttk"
msgstr ""
